heories\nare uplifts of the magical supergravity theories whose scalar manifolds are\nsymmetric spaces. The scalar manifolds of the other unified theories are not\nhomogeneous spaces. We also discuss the exceptional field theoretic\nformulations of non-metric unified $(1,0)$ tensor-Einstein supergravity\ntheories and conclude with speculations concerning the existence of higher\ndimensional non-metric supergravity theories that reduce to the $(4,0)$ theory\nin $d=6$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Sep 2020 22:51:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 29 May 2021 14:56:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-30"}
