uid-solid boundary on a reference grid. This reference\ngrid, typically a structured and uniform grid, is used to interpolate scattered\nhigh-dimensional field data as snapshot images. These input images are\nconvenient in training CRAN. This motivates us to further explore the\napplication of CRAN models for the prediction of fluid flows.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Sep 2020 06:54:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Sep 2020 05:45:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-23"}
